      <h2>A Thermador wall oven is a cabinet-integrated system. The repair approach matters.</h2>
      <p>The Thermador wall oven sitting in your kitchen was installed during the original build. The cabinetry around it was measured, cut, and trimmed to the oven's exact flush and reveal — often by the general contractor's finish carpenter, sometimes by a dedicated millwork shop. When that oven needs service eight or ten years later, how the technician approaches the job determines whether your kitchen stays intact.</p>
