      <h2>Thermador oven repair — common questions</h2>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>What does error E1, E2, E3, E4, or E5 mean?</summary>
        <p>E1 disables the self-clean cycle — usually the door-latch motor. E2 shuts off both heat and microwave on speed-oven combos — master control or communication fault. E3 and E4 turn off heat on the failed oven only — temperature sensor or heating circuit open. E5 is like E2 but triggered after microwave overheat protection. 60% of E-codes resolve to sensor or harness issues, not board replacements — we diagnose before swapping.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Do you service combi-steam ovens?</summary>
        <p>Yes — MES301HP, MES301HS, MES301JP, MED301JS, MED302JS, MED301JP, MED302JP, all the MED/MES Masterpiece and Professional steam models. Most combi-steam calls are sensor and descaling work, not parts. Real generator replacement is about 15% of the volume. Full service including descaling, steam-generator diagnosis, and element replacement.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Can you fix my oven without pulling it from the cabinet?</summary>
        <p>For most repairs, yes — door gasket, latch, heating element, convection fan, thermostat, control board, oven light. We pull the oven only for sealed-section work or heavy rear-compartment moisture damage. When we do pull it, we document the cabinetry before disassembly and reseat to factory flush spec.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How much does Thermador oven repair cost?</summary>
        <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Common repairs: bake element $195–$295, door gasket $245–$380, convection fan $340–$460, main control board $520–$780. Combi-steam descaling $245. See the pricing table on this page for the full list.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>My oven won't preheat past 200°F — what's wrong?</summary>
        <p>Usually one of three: failing bake element (visible break), temperature sensor reading falsely high (control cuts power thinking cavity is hot), or main-board relay intermittent. Diagnostic watches a full heating cycle with a calibrated thermocouple and identifies which component is the culprit. We don't guess.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Are Masterpiece and Professional different for repair?</summary>
        <p>Same core platform, different exterior trim. Core components — heating elements, fans, thermostats, controls, latches — are shared or compatible across Masterpiece (MED/ME/MES) and Professional (POD/PODMC). Main service difference is cosmetic: the door handle and bezel are different OEM parts. We carry parts that fit both series.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How fast can you come out?</summary>
        <p>Same-day on calls before 1 PM weekday inside regular coverage. Malibu and Pacific Palisades get next-morning priority. For a wall oven out before a holiday dinner — call and say so, we rearrange routing.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
